channel.title: Worried about this "SYIpkpker" thing, can anybody give me answers?
channel.description: Well today is the first day I hosted my server and out of nowhere in like 5 minutes of the server being up, that "SYIpkpker" guy loggs in and does his thing. Now what I'm really worried about is when he kept logging in my computer made a "beeping" noise so I just shut down the server immediately and now I'm here asking for answers. Has anybody have this happen to them....? He loggs in a bunch of times and my computer will make a beeping noise. Does anybody know what's going on, or what SYIpkpker has to do with my computer beeping? I really hope this is not a bad thing.

item.title: Worried about this "SYIpkpker" thing, can anybody give me answers?
item.dc:creator: @kihomura Kihomura
item.description:
@kihomura wrote:

Don’t worry, the SYI program can’t get into your computer, the beeping stands for your computer’s RAM hitting max, it can’t get onto your computer, because well, its just a thing for crashing servers, can’t do more than that, so don’t believe anyone that says something like “I’m going to SYI your computer” it’s a lie.
